<AUTHOR>David</AUTHOR>
<TEXT>Since 1985 I've owned an F-150 and four Silverados. By far the Honda is better built and more versatile. I don't need to tow my house or haul cattle. I park it instead of docking it. It is agile, and rides as well as my wife's Acura. We drove it to Colorado from Houston with another couple and the ladies' only complaint about the back seat was the height of the seatbelt anchors.</TEXT>
<FAVORITE>Steering feel, transmission smoothness and responsiveness. Five foot bed is plenty big.</FAVORITE>
