<DATE>08/13/2009</DATE>
<AUTHOR>Rick</AUTHOR>
<TEXT>Just completed a 3500 mile road trip with the wife and all the luggage that brings. Drove well on freeways and secondary roads, also did did well in the southwestern sun and downpours back east. Mileage was 19.4 for the trip and though it runs well at eighty the gas mileage really takes a hit. It is a tight vehicle with no rattles, vibrations or sqeaks. My general use other than road trips is around town and to the hardware store. Honda did well as this is one great truck.</TEXT>
<FAVORITE>The well laid out interior and center armrest/storage area was great for the little items. Rear seat bottoms that fold up were nice and we used that area for a cooler, jackets etc.</FAVORITE>
